own by FRR are consistent with topology; next-hop selection sometimes funnels through one spine from the super‑spine (this is a normal BGP path choice given the lab).\n- Packet latencies for successful pings were low (~3 ms), indicating no widespread congestion/latency issues on forwarding paths.\n\nConclusion\n- Network control plane is healthy and converged.\n- The observed data-plane failure between hosts is due to host-local packet corruption on pc_0_1 (netem corrupt 60%), causing packet loss and resulting RX drops at leaf_router_0_1:eth2. This is the root cause of the host connectivity issues.\n\n(End of diagnostic report)", "generation_info": {"finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 11862, "output_tokens": 2772, "total_tokens": 14634, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 11648}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 1472}}}
